# provision-wasp-saas Configuration
#
# USAGE - Two Options:
#
# Option 1 (RECOMMENDED): Use 1Password references
#   1. Fill in the op:// references below
#   2. Run commands with: op run --env-file=".env" -- npx provision-wasp-saas ...
#   3. The op CLI automatically resolves secrets before running
#
# Option 2: Use shell environment variables
#   1. Export variables directly: export CAPROVER_URL="..."
#   2. Run commands normally: npx provision-wasp-saas ...
#
# DO NOT mix both approaches! Choose one method.

# ============================================
# 1Password References (RECOMMENDED)
# ============================================
# Store secrets in 1Password and reference them here
# Format: op://vault-name/item-name/field-name
# Requires: op CLI installed and authenticated (op signin)

CAPROVER_URL="op://my-vault/CapRover/url"
CAPROVER_PASSWORD="op://my-vault/CapRover/password"
NEON_API_KEY="op://my-vault/Neon/api-key"
VERCEL_TOKEN="op://my-vault/Vercel/token"
RESEND_API_KEY="op://my-vault/Resend/api-key"

# Optional: Additional configuration
# NEON_ORG_ID="op://my-vault/Neon/org-id"
# NEON_REGION="aws-us-east-1"
# VERCEL_ORG_ID="op://my-vault/Vercel/org-id"

# Example commands with op run:
#   op run --env-file=".env" -- npx provision-wasp-saas --provision
#   op run --env-file=".env" -- npx provision-wasp-saas --cleanup-caprover --interactive

# ============================================
# Alternative: Direct Values (Less Secure)
# ============================================
# If not using 1Password, you can use direct values
# But consider using shell exports instead of storing in files

# CAPROVER_URL="https://captain.your-domain.com"
# CAPROVER_PASSWORD="your-caprover-password"
# NEON_API_KEY="your-neon-api-key"
# VERCEL_TOKEN="your-vercel-token"
# RESEND_API_KEY="your-resend-api-key"
